SDIT<br>
There is an organization of the sons and daughters of guys who never made it back.  It is helpful to talk with these kids (one of them is my kid).  They welcome any story with open arms...its all they have for fathers, stories, of what their dads might have been through, of who their dads might have been.  They harbor no resentment, only acceptance and interest.  They want to hear what you have to say.  You make it REAL for them, they might be an important connection for  you.  I don't know what you need, Dixie, but this is an incredible bunch of young adults.  Fathers Day at the Wall this year healed many with tears, the healing goes on and on. If interested, call (800) 984-9994      <br>

